  "text": "From the constructed graph we can extract task plans of a specific length [CITATION_1] which serve as a guide for the planner about how to travel between different subsets of G ∩ P. The planner, instead of exploring randomly how to go from one subset of G ∩ P to another, will follow those plans to search for a manipulation path of a specific number of transitions. Here a task plan is a sequence of graph nodes connected by graph edges. For example, from Fig. 2 a task plan of length 3 to travel from (6, 6) to (2, 2) is given by (6, 6) → (4, 6) → (4, 2) → (2, 2).",
